The government's responsibility is not only information disclosure, but also in the face of sudden public health events, the Organization of Response Measures, planning is in place

By Zhu Tao, editor, Caijing

"All sides are not satisfied with the disclosure of our information, " Zhou Xianwang, Wuhan's mayor, admitted in an interview with CCTV on the afternoon of January 27 that Wuhan had an untimely disclosure in the COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic. "As a local government, I can not disclose information until I have obtained it and authorized it, " he explained

According to the latest information from the National Health Commission, as of 2400 hours on January 29, the National Health Commission has received a total of 7,711 confirmed cases, 170 cumulative deaths, 124 cumulative cured discharged cases, a total of 12,167 suspected cases. A total of 25 confirmed cases were reported from Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan.

Some people believe that releasing authoritative and accurate information in time can alleviate public anxiety, lead public to respond positively and rationally, at the same time dispel public doubt and avoid mass panic. Therefore, if the official timely disclosure of the epidemic, it is bound to reduce the spread of the disease.

So, who has the authority to declare an outbreak?

WHO has the right to release information about the outbreak?

Back in time, the first official announcement of "Wuhan Pneumonia" came 23 days or more after the first case of COVID-19 pneumonia in Wuhan.

On December 30,2019, "pneumonia of unknown cause" in Wuhan came into public view due to two red-headed documents posted on the Internet. The document was signed by the medical and Health Administration branch of the Wuhan Board of Health, under the theme "report to the hospital for treatment of pneumonia of unknown cause" . There have been 27 cases of pneumonia of unknown origin in the South China Seafood Market in Wuhan, with seven in serious condition, the documents show.

The next day, Wuhan City Health Commission for the first time issued a notification of the epidemic situation of pneumonia. On the morning of the same day, the National Health Commission Expert Group arrived in Wuhan to start relevant testing and verification work.

The earliest case to show symptoms was December 8,2019, according to the Wuhan Municipal Health and Health Commission. Several recent studies suggest that the date could be even earlier.

"clinical characteristics of COVID-19 in Wuhan, China in 2019, " said Huang Chaolin, chief of Thoracic Surgery, Jinyintan Hospital, Wuhan, in an article published online by the Lancet on January 24, the first infected person admitted to Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital had onset of symptoms dating back to December 1,2019, and there was no history of exposure to the south China Seafood Market, nor did his family members develop fever and respiratory symptoms; only three others developed symptoms until December 10,2019, two of them also had no exposure to the south China seafood market.

Taking into account the time lag between infection and symptom onset, the first human infection must have occurred in November 2019, which means, according to Danyll Lucy, an infectious disease specialist at the Georgetown University in the United States, by then, the virus may have been quietly circulating among people until late December, when a massive outbreak at the south China seafood market erupted.

From the point of view of reporting procedures, "disclosure after authorization" is indeed a legal basis.

According to the law on the prevention and control of Infectious Diseases, the Health Administration Department under the State Council regularly publishes information on Epidemic Situations of infectious diseases throughout the country. The Government of the People's Republic of China of provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the Central Government regularly publishes information on the epidemic situation of infectious diseases in their respective administrative areas. In the event of an outbreak or epidemic of an infectious disease, the Health Administration Department under the State Council shall be responsible for releasing information on the epidemic situation of an infectious disease to the public, it may also authorize the Government of the People's Republic of China of a province, autonomous region or municipality directly under the central government to make public information on the epidemic situation of infectious diseases in its administrative area.

Article twenty-five of the Regulations on emergency response to public health emergencies and article thirty-two of the measures for the administration of information reporting on the surveillance of public health emergencies and infectious diseases make the same provisions for the main body of information disclosure on infectious diseases.

That is to say, the main body that issues information about infectious diseases includes the health administrative department of the State Council and the authorized health administrative departments of provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the central government.

According to the administrative territorial entity classification, Wuhan is classified as a sub-province-level division city and a administrative territorial entity city, not as a province, autonomous region or municipality directly under the central government, based on existing laws and regulations, said Li Zhiguang, a lawyer with the Beijing Kyoto Law Firm, wuhan's Health Administration is not the subject of the announcement, so the Mayor of Wuhan has no power to make the announcement.

Li Zhiguang thinks, epidemic situation information announces main body to set too high, add prophase to report a procedure long and low efficiency, easy to cause epidemic situation information to announce lag. He suggested lowering the threshold for disclosure of subjects, for example, for Class A infectious diseases as defined in the law on prevention and control of infectious diseases and Class B infectious diseases for which prevention and control measures for Class A infectious diseases are taken, the information on the epidemic situation can be made public directly by the Municipal Health Administration Department, at the same time, the Higher Health Administrative Department and the State Council Health Administrative Department should be reported to shorten the flow of information disclosure of the epidemic situation.

Wu Weixin, director of the Jinhua Center for Disease Control and Prevention, and others have also written that when an outbreak or epidemic of an infectious disease occurs in a certain place, it will have a certain impact on the local area, and its severity is not serious enough to be announced by the Health Administration Department at or above the provincial level, but when the local people urgently need to know the epidemic information, because the local health administration department does not have the authority to announce, then the epidemic information has no department to announce.

Regarding the disclosure of information on the epidemic situation, Xu Shuqiang, director of the Emergency Response Office of the National Health Commission, said on January 22 that after the outbreak of the epidemic, under the guidance of the National Commission of Health and Human Resources, the Wuhan Municipal Commission of Health and Human Resources released information on the epidemic situation and prevention and control on December 31,2019 and January 3,5 and 9,2020. At the same time, according to the development of the epidemic situation, daily updates were issued from January 11.

Until January 20, when the State Council convened an executive meeting to confirm COVID-19 as a category B infectious disease and to manage category a infectious disease, and demand that the territories take responsibility, Zhou told CCTV, wuhan Aspect "the work took the initiative to be many" .

According to public information, it is unclear exactly when and how Wuhan reported the outbreak after it occurred.

Government responsibility in the epidemic

Wang Ling, a lawyer at Beijing Cailiang Law Firm who specializes in administrative law, said the government's responsibility is not just to disclose information, but also to organize and respond to public health emergencies. The Wuhan Municipal Government shall carry out prevention and control in accordance with the preventive and control plans, control the development and spread of the epidemic situation, make overall plans and coordination, organize rescue personnel and prepare treatment sites, and to ensure that masks, protective clothing, vegetables, food and other necessary supplies in place.

Regarding the disclosure of the epidemic situation, Wang Ling said that if only the law on the prevention and control of infectious diseases was applied, it should indeed be reported to the National Health Commission first, according to the Mayor of Wuhan, and then authorized by the National Health Commission to make the announcement. However, the law on emergency response, which came into force in November 2007, provides that when the possibility of an impending or impending occurrence of a natural disaster, an accident disaster or a public health event that can be forewarned of increases, local Government of the People's Republic of China at or above the county level shall, in accordance with the relevant laws, administrative regulations and the limits of authority and procedures prescribed by the State Council, issue an alarm at the corresponding level, and decide and announce that the area concerned shall enter an early warning period, at the same time report to the Government of the People's Republic of China, if necessary, report to the higher level, and to the local garrison and may be endangered adjacent or relevant areas of Government of the People's Republic of China.

After entering the early warning period, what measures should the local government take? As far as information disclosure is concerned, the emergency response law clearly states that after issuing a three-and four-level alert and declaring an early warning period, the local government shall "announce to the public the channels through which information on emergencies is reflected, and strengthen the monitoring, forecasting and early warning of the occurrence and development of Emergencies" ; and issue first-and second-level warnings, and declare that after the early warning period has been entered, the local government shall "timely issue to the society suggestions and advice on taking specific measures to avoid or mitigate the harm" .

According to the law, relevant departments in Hubei Province and Wuhan should take corresponding measures according to category B Infectious Diseases before the National Health Commission reports them to the State Council for approval of Category A infectious disease management, Wang said. In addition, when the epidemic is perceived to be serious and pose a great threat to society, emergency plans should be activated, timely warnings issued, the whole process of the epidemic open, and provide a path for public participation.

"Infectious Disease Prevention Law" requires "authorized disclosure" , "Emergency Response Law" requires timely warning, the two laws are inconsistent?

There is no conflict between the two laws, Wang said. Before obtaining the authorization from the National Health Commission for the announcement of the epidemic situation, the Hubei Health Administration Department, in accordance with the law on the prevention and control of infectious diseases, can not declare whether the epidemic situation belongs to Class A or class B infectious diseases. However, in accordance with the law on emergency response, they should perform their statutory duties in response to public health emergencies, initiate emergency response plans and timely issue warning information to the public, how many people in Wuhan are being harmed by an unknown virus, for example, and to remind everyone that the harm may be transmissible. On the other hand, while the State Department has not yet determined that COVID-19 pneumonia can be prevented and controlled as a class B infectious disease, Wuhan was able to treat it as a class B infectious disease until early December, it could have done so when the first case was confirmed in Wuhan, which has a history of SARS, and which published a study on Covid-19 last year that should have shown that the virus is similar to SARS.

Wang Hufeng, director of the Center for Medical Reform Research at Renmin University of China, said in an interview with Caijing, in fact, as early as 2006, the State has already delegated the authority of primary and secondary response to public health emergencies to provincial governments; Level Four Response Authority is county level.

It is based on the Ministry of Health's Official infectious, which has been in force since 2006.

In 2003, the Ministry of Health (Moh) organized and formulated the Ministry of Health's Information Dissemination Program on Official infectious and public health emergencies (for trial implementation) , due to the provisions of Article thirty-eight of the newly amended Law on the Prevention and control of infectious diseases, "the state shall establish the system of information disclosure of infectious diseases epidemic situation" , and the specific requirements of the National Public Health Emergency Response Plan, the Ministry of Health revised the original programme and published it on March 3,2006. One of the important amendments is that, "The Ministry of Health has authorized the health administrative departments of all provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the central government to release timely and accurate information on infectious disease outbreaks, epidemics and other public health emergencies within their respective administrative areas, " the statement said

Wang said that is why the provinces have recently adopted a first-level response, rather than the State Council unified arrangements for a first-level response. However, it is worth noting that on January 23, Hunan and Guangdong provinces, which are not the outbreak areas, have already started the first-level emergency response to public health emergencies, and as the outbreak areas, the Hubei provincial government launched a Level 2 emergency response on Jan. 22, and did not upgrade from Level 2 to level 1 until Jan. 24.

Wang Hufeng believes the delay in announcing the outbreak in Wuhan is not about whether Wuhan should follow legal procedures, but whether officials have done their duty within the scope of their duties.

Wang said that the law has provisions, officials can only do things in accordance with the current law; as for the law does not have explicit provisions, we have to deal with the actual situation. Even if higher authorities do not identify the disease, local officials should take preventive and control measures within their areas of responsibility for suspected infectious diseases with knowledge.

Wuhan's control and Prevention Timeline for COVID-19. More than 40,000 families served 13,986 dishes at a 10,000-family dinner held in Wuhan's Baibu Pavilion Community on Jan. 18, filling the main venue and nine branch venues of the Party and Masses Activity Center, the Beijing News reported.

Wuhan has also launched the 2020 Spring Festival time in Wuhan, with the theme "a strong Chinese wind warms the warm river city" . Starting from January 20,200,000 vouchers will be distributed to citizens for travel and travel, free visits to major cultural and tourist attractions during the Lunar New Year holidays. After the controversy, Wuhan Municipal Bureau of Culture and tourism issued an emergency notice, announcement activities postponed.

On January 21st, after it became clear that the COVID-19 would be passed on from one person to another, many places in Hubei, including Wuhan, had to close the city, but at the same time, the 2020 Hubei Spring Festival party was held at the Hongshan District Auditorium.

All three incidents were cited as adverse to epidemic prevention and control, as well as improper handling of public health emergencies.
